WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.000
Moving house.

00:07.000 --> 00:14.000
A cup of tea?

00:14.000 --> 00:16.000
Yes dear.

00:16.000 --> 00:18.000
Ah.

00:18.000 --> 00:21.000
Yeah, Stuart.

00:21.000 --> 00:23.000
Here you are.

00:23.000 --> 00:25.000
Yes dear.

00:25.000 --> 00:27.000
Oh.

00:28.000 --> 00:31.000
I'll go and open the door for Boris, Josie.

00:31.000 --> 00:33.000
Why do I have to do it?

00:33.000 --> 00:36.000
Don't argue. Just do it.

00:40.000 --> 00:42.000
Get down Boris.

00:42.000 --> 00:43.000
Here you are Boris.

00:43.000 --> 00:44.000
Have my piece of toast.

00:44.000 --> 00:48.000
Don't feed him at the table, Josie.

00:48.000 --> 00:53.000
There's another competition in the newspaper I can enter Nancy.

00:53.000 --> 00:55.000
What can you win this time?

00:55.000 --> 00:58.000
A ticket for a Marilyn Manson concert.

00:58.000 --> 01:00.000
Do you know who that is?

01:00.000 --> 01:05.000
No, but isn't she a singer? A bit like Nanamoo Scory.

01:05.000 --> 01:09.000
Yes, that's right. Just like her. I hope you win.

01:09.000 --> 01:12.000
Oh, just ignore him mum.

01:12.000 --> 01:18.000
Nancy, it says here that your day is going to be full of fun and laughter.

01:18.000 --> 01:20.000
I don't think so.

01:20.000 --> 01:23.000
Why do you look at the horoscope every day mum?

01:23.000 --> 01:27.000
It's fun. Let me look at Josephine's stars.

01:27.000 --> 01:29.000
Oh yes, here it is.

01:29.000 --> 01:35.000
It says that you're feeling off colour today and it's better to stay indoors.

01:35.000 --> 01:39.000
Yeah, you're right, Grand. I have a stomach ache.

01:39.000 --> 01:41.000
I'm not going to school today.

01:41.000 --> 01:44.000
Stop that Josephine. You are going to school. No arguments.

01:44.000 --> 01:48.000
Oh, why do I have to go to school? I hate it. It's boring.

01:48.000 --> 01:49.000
Because you do.

01:49.000 --> 01:51.000
I hated school too.

01:51.000 --> 01:55.000
The teachers were terrible. They used to cane us with sticks.

01:55.000 --> 01:57.000
Oh, do they cane you, Grand?

01:57.000 --> 02:01.000
Yes, of course. I was cained by the headmaster.

02:01.000 --> 02:07.000
What was his name? Oh yes, Mr. Payne. I put some glue on a seat.

02:07.000 --> 02:10.000
That's not so bad. Why did he cane you?

02:10.000 --> 02:12.000
Because it was the teacher's toilet seat.

02:12.000 --> 02:15.000
Really? Wow.

02:15.000 --> 02:20.000
Don't get ideas, Josephine. Go and get ready for school.

02:20.000 --> 02:22.000
Mom, please.

02:22.000 --> 02:26.000
Do as I tell you now.

02:26.000 --> 02:29.000
Teenagers.

02:29.000 --> 02:33.000
And put that newspaper down, Pete.

02:33.000 --> 02:35.000
Sorry? Is there a problem?

02:35.000 --> 02:37.000
No, no.

02:37.000 --> 02:41.000
I was just trying to get our daughter to go to school.

02:41.000 --> 02:44.000
Thank you for helping me.

02:44.000 --> 02:47.000
It's OK, dear. I'm always happy to help.

02:47.000 --> 02:49.000
Can you pass the toast, please?

02:49.000 --> 02:51.000
Didn't you hear what I said?

02:51.000 --> 02:54.000
Yes, dear, of course, dear. And the tree core, please.

02:54.000 --> 02:56.000
Here it is.

02:56.000 --> 03:01.000
Ow! Why did you do that? Look, it's all over my trousers.

03:01.000 --> 03:04.000
I don't believe it. Get down, Boris.

03:04.000 --> 03:07.000
I'm not playing. To something.

03:07.000 --> 03:10.000
Go to work now, Pete, before I do something else to you.

03:10.000 --> 03:14.000
The next time, it might be a kitchen knife, so be careful in future.

03:14.000 --> 03:16.000
What's the matter? What did I do?

03:16.000 --> 03:21.000
Nothing, Pete. Absolutely nothing. That's the problem.

03:21.000 --> 03:24.000
I'm going. Good-bye.

03:31.000 --> 03:33.000
Why did you marry him, Nancy?

03:33.000 --> 03:35.000
Do you want someone you as well?

03:35.000 --> 03:38.000
I always said he was bone idle.

03:38.000 --> 03:43.000
I liked that lawyer you went out with once. Nice eyes and a lovely smile.

03:43.000 --> 03:46.000
Do you hear what you think, Mum?

03:46.000 --> 03:50.000
Ooh! It's not a good day for Pete.

03:50.000 --> 03:54.000
It says in his horoscope that he gets some bad news this afternoon.

03:54.000 --> 03:57.000
Stop it, Mum. Don't make things worse.

03:57.000 --> 04:00.000
I must tell Pete. He must be careful.

04:04.000 --> 04:05.000
Nancy.

04:05.000 --> 04:08.000
Yes? What do you want now?

04:08.000 --> 04:11.000
I can't find any clean trousers.

04:11.000 --> 04:14.000
They're in the fridge between the cheese and the tomatoes.

04:14.000 --> 04:17.000
Why are they in the fridge?

04:17.000 --> 04:20.000
Where do you think they are? In the bedroom.

04:20.000 --> 04:23.000
Left wardrobe on the right, where they always are.

04:23.000 --> 04:24.000
Thank you, Nancy.

04:24.000 --> 04:26.000
Pete. Yes? What do you want?

04:26.000 --> 04:30.000
Be careful. Today is a bad day for you.

04:30.000 --> 04:31.000
Sorry?

04:31.000 --> 04:34.000
It says in your horoscope that you get some bad news.

04:34.000 --> 04:38.000
Not that rubbish again. I'm not interested.

04:39.000 --> 04:41.000
Wait a minute.

04:41.000 --> 04:43.000
Do you believe all that rubbish in the horoscope?

04:43.000 --> 04:45.000
Sometimes it's true, you know.

04:45.000 --> 04:48.000
Well, you're the same star sign as me, so you be careful.

04:48.000 --> 04:51.000
Ooh dear, I forgot.

04:51.000 --> 04:53.000
Maybe you fall down the stairs.

04:53.000 --> 04:55.000
Maybe Boris bites your leg.

04:55.000 --> 04:57.000
Maybe your hearing aid explodes.

04:57.000 --> 04:58.000
Maybe.

04:58.000 --> 04:59.000
Goodbye.

04:59.000 --> 05:01.000
I'll find it.

05:01.000 --> 05:02.000
They dirty deed.

05:09.000 --> 05:11.000
I told you not to say anything.

05:11.000 --> 05:14.000
Now, where is Josephine? She's going to be late.

05:14.000 --> 05:17.000
Can you go upstairs and tell us a hurry up, please, Mum?

05:17.000 --> 05:20.000
I have to make her sandwiches.

05:20.000 --> 05:22.000
Oh, what a family.

05:22.000 --> 05:24.000
OK, Nancy.

05:24.000 --> 05:26.000
Come on, Boris.

05:26.000 --> 05:27.000
There's a good dog.

05:27.000 --> 05:30.000
You don't want to bite my leg, do you?

05:39.000 --> 05:42.000
Oh, there you are, Josie.

05:42.000 --> 05:44.000
Come on, your mother is waiting.

05:44.000 --> 05:47.000
Josh, close the door, Grand.

05:47.000 --> 05:49.000
Can you keep a secret?

05:49.000 --> 05:51.000
Oh, I love secrets.

05:51.000 --> 05:53.000
Come here.

05:53.000 --> 05:55.000
Look here.

05:55.000 --> 05:57.000
In this box.

05:57.000 --> 06:01.000
Oh, it's Robbie the Rat.

06:01.000 --> 06:02.000
I thought...

06:02.000 --> 06:03.000
Yes, we know.

06:03.000 --> 06:04.000
Dad told me to sell him.

06:04.000 --> 06:06.000
But I want to keep him.

06:06.000 --> 06:08.000
Oh, he's so sweet.

06:08.000 --> 06:13.000
Oh, look at his lovely little eyes and funny nose.

06:13.000 --> 06:16.000
He really looks like your father.

06:16.000 --> 06:20.000
Don't tell Mum or Daddy's here in my room.

06:20.000 --> 06:21.000
Please?

06:21.000 --> 06:22.000
I promise.

06:22.000 --> 06:25.000
It's our secret.

06:26.000 --> 06:36.000
It's nice to put my feet up for a moment.

06:36.000 --> 06:38.000
You work too hard.

06:38.000 --> 06:42.000
Pete and Josephine should do more around the house to help you.

06:42.000 --> 06:44.000
Stop it, Mum.

06:44.000 --> 06:47.000
Can you pass me another biscuit, please?

06:47.000 --> 06:52.000
I just want a few minutes of peace and quiet.

06:53.000 --> 06:55.000
Oh, dear.

06:55.000 --> 06:57.000
I wonder who that is.

06:57.000 --> 06:59.000
Can you answer it, Mum?

06:59.000 --> 07:02.000
All right.

07:02.000 --> 07:04.000
Hello?

07:04.000 --> 07:06.000
Who is it?

07:06.000 --> 07:07.000
Sorry.

07:07.000 --> 07:09.000
Pete.

07:09.000 --> 07:10.000
Speak up.

07:10.000 --> 07:11.000
What does he want?

07:11.000 --> 07:13.000
Sorry?

07:13.000 --> 07:14.000
Yes.

07:14.000 --> 07:15.000
All right.

07:15.000 --> 07:16.000
Bye.

07:16.000 --> 07:17.000
Yes?

07:17.000 --> 07:20.000
He said he's coming home now.

07:20.000 --> 07:21.000
But what did he want?

07:21.000 --> 07:24.000
Something about he forgot the bag.

07:24.000 --> 07:26.000
What are you talking about, Mother?

07:26.000 --> 07:28.000
It was a terrible line.

07:28.000 --> 07:31.000
All I could hear was the sound of cars.

07:31.000 --> 07:33.000
I think he was phoning with his mobile.

07:33.000 --> 07:35.000
His what?

07:35.000 --> 07:36.000
It's, er...

07:36.000 --> 07:38.000
Oh, it doesn't matter.

07:38.000 --> 07:41.000
I want to know why he's coming home.

07:41.000 --> 07:44.000
It's only two o'clock in the afternoon.

07:44.000 --> 07:47.000
I told you today was going to be a bad day.

07:47.000 --> 07:49.000
I can feel it in my bones.

07:49.000 --> 07:52.000
I wonder what happened at work.

07:52.000 --> 07:55.000
It must be serious, don't worry.

07:55.000 --> 07:57.000
He just forgot something, I think.

07:57.000 --> 07:59.000
Yes, you're right.

07:59.000 --> 08:00.000
Okay.

08:00.000 --> 08:02.000
I can't sit around anymore.

08:02.000 --> 08:06.000
I can make Josephine's bed and tidy her room.

08:06.000 --> 08:07.000
Thanks, Mum.

08:11.000 --> 08:13.000
Can you change the sheets, please?

08:13.000 --> 08:15.000
Yes, Nancy.

08:19.000 --> 08:23.000
Now, where are you, you little thing?

08:25.000 --> 08:27.000
Oh, there you are.

08:27.000 --> 08:30.000
Oh, you're so sweet and cute.

08:30.000 --> 08:32.000
Come here.

08:32.000 --> 08:34.000
Oh, it tickles.

08:37.000 --> 08:39.000
Stop it, Boris.

08:39.000 --> 08:41.000
Here, Robbie.

08:41.000 --> 08:42.000
Don't be afraid.

08:42.000 --> 08:44.000
What's that, Mum?

08:44.000 --> 08:45.000
Nothing.

08:45.000 --> 08:46.000
Nothing.

08:47.000 --> 08:49.000
Oh, don't do that.

08:49.000 --> 08:50.000
Come out.

08:50.000 --> 08:52.000
Oh, that tickles.

08:52.000 --> 08:54.000
How are you?

08:54.000 --> 08:56.000
Oh, come out of my jumper.

08:56.000 --> 08:58.000
Oh, no, stop that.

09:00.000 --> 09:02.000
What's happening in here?

09:02.000 --> 09:04.000
Oh, no, stop that.

09:04.000 --> 09:07.000
Oh, get off, Boris.

09:07.000 --> 09:09.000
Oh, bad.

09:09.000 --> 09:11.000
What's the matter with everyone in this house?

09:11.000 --> 09:13.000
Who are you talking to, Mum?

09:13.000 --> 09:15.000
Oh, that tickles, stop it.

09:15.000 --> 09:16.000
What's happening?

09:16.000 --> 09:17.000
I'm home.

09:17.000 --> 09:19.000
What's the noise?

09:19.000 --> 09:20.000
Oh, hello, Pete.

09:20.000 --> 09:21.000
I'm coming.

09:24.000 --> 09:25.000
Is that your mother?

09:25.000 --> 09:26.000
Yes.

09:26.000 --> 09:28.000
I don't know what she's doing.

09:28.000 --> 09:30.000
Maybe she'll head Sherry on her cornflakes.

09:30.000 --> 09:33.000
She's a Josephine's room, laughing her head off,

09:33.000 --> 09:35.000
and I don't know why.

09:35.000 --> 09:37.000
Boris is sitting looking at her.

09:39.000 --> 09:41.000
She's getting old, Nancy.

09:41.000 --> 09:44.000
Maybe we should start looking for an old fossils home for her.

09:44.000 --> 09:45.000
Oh, don't start that again.

09:45.000 --> 09:47.000
You know I get angry.

09:47.000 --> 09:49.000
Mum is staying with us,

09:49.000 --> 09:53.000
and they are called old people's homes, not old fossils homes.

09:53.000 --> 09:55.000
Well, I think we seriously...

09:55.000 --> 09:57.000
We can talk about this another time.

09:57.000 --> 09:59.000
Why are you home so early?

09:59.000 --> 10:01.000
You've never come home at this time.

10:01.000 --> 10:03.000
Oh, yes.

10:03.000 --> 10:06.000
Look, can we go into the kitchen?

10:06.000 --> 10:09.000
I can't concentrate with a laughing hyena upstairs.

10:12.000 --> 10:14.000
Sit down, dear.

10:14.000 --> 10:16.000
Would you like a cup of tea?

10:16.000 --> 10:19.000
Something stronger might be a better idea.

10:19.000 --> 10:20.000
Why?

10:20.000 --> 10:21.000
What happened this morning?

10:21.000 --> 10:23.000
Tell me, please.

10:23.000 --> 10:25.000
I lost my job.

10:25.000 --> 10:26.000
What?

10:26.000 --> 10:27.000
Yes.

10:27.000 --> 10:28.000
I lost my job.

10:28.000 --> 10:30.000
I am now unemployed.

10:30.000 --> 10:32.000
Six of us from the office got the sack.

10:32.000 --> 10:34.000
We can work until the end of the month,

10:34.000 --> 10:37.000
and then thank you, but goodbye.

10:38.000 --> 10:40.000
But I don't understand.

10:40.000 --> 10:44.000
Oh, that's what you were trying to tell mum on the phone.

10:44.000 --> 10:47.000
She thought you said you forgot the bag.

10:47.000 --> 10:50.000
She's deaf as well as losing her marbles.

10:50.000 --> 10:51.000
Beat.

10:51.000 --> 10:53.000
OK, OK.

10:53.000 --> 10:54.000
Well, as I was saying,

10:54.000 --> 10:56.000
the company needs to save money,

10:56.000 --> 10:59.000
and my department is being closed.

10:59.000 --> 11:01.000
What are we going to do?

11:01.000 --> 11:03.000
I can find another job.

11:03.000 --> 11:04.000
I hope.

11:04.000 --> 11:06.000
I think we must move house, though.

11:06.000 --> 11:09.000
This one is too big and too expensive.

11:09.000 --> 11:11.000
We must save money.

11:11.000 --> 11:12.000
Wait a minute.

11:12.000 --> 11:14.000
I need to think.

11:14.000 --> 11:16.000
Be quiet, mother.

11:16.000 --> 11:19.000
I'm just going to shut my mother up.

11:20.000 --> 11:23.000
I'm just going to shut my mother up.

11:32.000 --> 11:34.000
What is the matter with you?

11:34.000 --> 11:36.000
Calm down, please.

11:36.000 --> 11:37.000
Stop it.

11:37.000 --> 11:40.000
Calm down and come downstairs.

11:40.000 --> 11:42.000
Peter's lost his job.

11:42.000 --> 11:43.000
Oh, no.

11:43.000 --> 11:45.000
I knew today it was a bad day.

11:45.000 --> 11:47.000
Why are you laughing?

11:48.000 --> 11:50.000
Yes, you are.

11:50.000 --> 11:51.000
No, I'm not.

11:51.000 --> 11:53.000
It's terrible.

11:53.000 --> 11:55.000
Oh, this is impossible.

11:55.000 --> 11:57.000
Stay there.

12:10.000 --> 12:12.000
Here you are, Boris.

12:12.000 --> 12:16.000
There might be the last time you have meat for your dinner.

12:18.000 --> 12:20.000
What are we going to do, Boris?

12:20.000 --> 12:23.000
I wonder what we're going to do.

12:23.000 --> 12:26.000
I'm home.

12:26.000 --> 12:28.000
I'm hungry.

12:28.000 --> 12:31.000
School is bloody boring.

12:31.000 --> 12:33.000
Teachers are so dumb.

12:33.000 --> 12:35.000
I don't know anything.

12:35.000 --> 12:36.000
I'm starving.

12:36.000 --> 12:37.000
I want some crisps.

12:37.000 --> 12:40.000
If you wait five minutes, Josie, you can have something cooked.

12:40.000 --> 12:41.000
I'm making a curry.

12:41.000 --> 12:43.000
No, crisps are great.

12:43.000 --> 12:46.000
I want to find Julia.

12:47.000 --> 12:49.000
She was at school all day today with you.

12:49.000 --> 12:50.000
Can't she wait?

12:50.000 --> 12:51.000
I want to talk to you.

12:51.000 --> 12:52.000
See ya.

12:52.000 --> 12:54.000
But Jo?

12:55.000 --> 12:58.000
It's easier to have a conversation with you, Boris.

12:59.000 --> 13:00.000
Boris?

13:00.000 --> 13:02.000
Boris?

13:02.000 --> 13:04.000
Come back, Boris.

13:05.000 --> 13:07.000
When is dinner?

13:07.000 --> 13:08.000
In five minutes.

13:08.000 --> 13:09.000
Okay.

13:09.000 --> 13:11.000
I just need to finish some repairs on the car.

13:11.000 --> 13:12.000
That can wait.

13:12.000 --> 13:15.000
There are more important things to talk about.

13:15.000 --> 13:16.000
Like what?

13:16.000 --> 13:19.000
What planet do you live on, Pete?

13:19.000 --> 13:22.000
At the end of the month, you have no job.

13:22.000 --> 13:23.000
Oh, yes.

13:23.000 --> 13:24.000
I forgot.

13:24.000 --> 13:25.000
You forgot?

13:25.000 --> 13:27.000
Don't you think we need to talk about it?

13:27.000 --> 13:29.000
I suppose so.

13:29.000 --> 13:32.000
Where do we move to?

13:32.000 --> 13:35.000
What do we say to Josie and Mum?

13:35.000 --> 13:37.000
I went to the estate agent some way home.

13:37.000 --> 13:42.000
I got some information about a really nice two bedroom flat in Cedar Road near the park.

13:42.000 --> 13:44.000
Why didn't you ask me to come?

13:44.000 --> 13:46.000
I am your wife, you know.

13:46.000 --> 13:49.000
When we sell the house, we can easily buy this flat.

13:49.000 --> 13:52.000
It's got a nice balcony and a small garden.

13:52.000 --> 13:55.000
You know you are always saying that the garden here is too big.

13:55.000 --> 13:56.000
There's too much cleaning and...

13:56.000 --> 13:58.000
Yes, yes, I know.

13:58.000 --> 14:00.000
We can go and look at the flat this evening.

14:00.000 --> 14:01.000
Okay.

14:02.000 --> 14:03.000
Wait a minute.

14:03.000 --> 14:06.000
How many bedrooms did you say the flat has?

14:06.000 --> 14:07.000
Back in a minute.

14:07.000 --> 14:09.000
You've got to do something in the garage.

14:09.000 --> 14:12.000
Did you say two bedrooms?

14:12.000 --> 14:13.000
But...

14:13.000 --> 14:15.000
Where does my mother sleep?

14:15.000 --> 14:16.000
Ooh.

14:16.000 --> 14:19.000
I feel a little strange.

14:19.000 --> 14:22.000
My muscles ache from so much laughing.

14:22.000 --> 14:25.000
Still don't understand why you were laughing.

14:25.000 --> 14:28.000
I think I need a little sherry to calm my nerves.

14:28.000 --> 14:29.000
Back in a minute.

14:29.000 --> 14:31.000
What a house.

14:31.000 --> 14:33.000
It's like a railway station.

14:33.000 --> 14:34.000
I'm so hungry.

14:34.000 --> 14:35.000
I want some biscuits.

14:35.000 --> 14:37.000
Just sit down, Josephine.

14:37.000 --> 14:39.000
You can have some biscuits in a minute.

14:39.000 --> 14:41.000
Pete?

14:41.000 --> 14:42.000
Mom?

14:42.000 --> 14:44.000
Come in the kitchen.

14:44.000 --> 14:46.000
Now!

14:46.000 --> 14:49.000
I said now!

14:49.000 --> 14:51.000
Keep your hair on, Mom.

14:51.000 --> 14:52.000
Chill out.

14:52.000 --> 14:55.000
How can I chill out when your father's lost his job today?

14:55.000 --> 14:56.000
What?

14:56.000 --> 14:57.000
Yes.

14:57.000 --> 14:58.000
You heard me.

14:58.000 --> 15:00.000
We have to move soon.

15:00.000 --> 15:01.000
Find a smaller house.

15:01.000 --> 15:02.000
I want my own room.

15:02.000 --> 15:03.000
Yes, of course.

15:03.000 --> 15:05.000
I'm not sharing with anyone.

15:05.000 --> 15:07.000
Oh, that's better.

15:07.000 --> 15:08.000
A little sherry.

15:08.000 --> 15:09.000
It always helps.

15:09.000 --> 15:10.000
Can you sit down?

15:10.000 --> 15:12.000
Please, Mother.

15:12.000 --> 15:14.000
Perhaps you need a sherry too?

15:14.000 --> 15:16.000
No, I don't.

15:16.000 --> 15:18.000
What's the problem, Nancy?

15:18.000 --> 15:21.000
Can we all sit down together?

15:21.000 --> 15:23.000
Good.

15:23.000 --> 15:25.000
Right.

15:25.000 --> 15:27.000
Listen.

15:27.000 --> 15:31.000
In a few weeks, Pete has no job.

15:31.000 --> 15:33.000
We have to move.

15:33.000 --> 15:36.000
Oh, what a terrible day.

15:36.000 --> 15:38.000
And you bad things were going to happen.

15:38.000 --> 15:39.000
Be quiet, Mother.

15:39.000 --> 15:40.000
Please.

15:40.000 --> 15:43.000
Yes, and I know the perfect place for us.

15:43.000 --> 15:45.000
It's in Cedar Road next to the park.

15:45.000 --> 15:47.000
I'm very close to your school, Josie.

15:47.000 --> 15:49.000
And the city centre.

15:49.000 --> 15:50.000
It's perfect.

15:50.000 --> 15:53.000
My friend, Julia, is just around the corner.

15:53.000 --> 15:54.000
Great.

15:54.000 --> 15:56.000
Cedar Road is near the Bingo Club.

15:56.000 --> 15:58.000
I can walk there.

15:58.000 --> 16:00.000
I don't need to get a taxi.

16:00.000 --> 16:01.000
I don't like taxis.

16:01.000 --> 16:02.000
Tax is always smelly.

16:02.000 --> 16:03.000
Yes.

16:03.000 --> 16:04.000
Okay, Mom.

16:04.000 --> 16:08.000
But the problem is that the flat Pete found has only got.

16:08.000 --> 16:11.000
And Boris can walk in the park.

16:11.000 --> 16:18.000
As I was saying, the flat Pete found for us only five minutes to walk to the shops.

16:18.000 --> 16:21.000
It only has two bedrooms.

16:21.000 --> 16:24.000
Oh, no.

16:24.000 --> 16:27.000
I don't want to go into an old people's home.

16:27.000 --> 16:29.000
They're full of old people.

16:29.000 --> 16:30.000
Don't worry, Mom.

16:30.000 --> 16:32.000
You don't have to go into a home.

16:32.000 --> 16:34.000
There isn't any other alternative.

16:34.000 --> 16:36.000
Yes, there is.

16:36.000 --> 16:38.000
I'm sure we can find another solution.

16:38.000 --> 16:41.000
Sorry, but you're going to have to go into the home.

16:41.000 --> 16:42.000
That's life.

16:42.000 --> 16:44.000
It's all right.

16:44.000 --> 16:46.000
I know you don't want me here.

16:46.000 --> 16:52.000
Last week, John, my friend at Bingo, said I can go and live with him.

16:52.000 --> 16:57.000
He needs someone to help him, as he can't see very well.

16:57.000 --> 16:58.000
He's blind.

16:58.000 --> 17:00.000
Good thing too.

17:00.000 --> 17:02.000
Are you sure you want to do that, Mom?

17:02.000 --> 17:04.000
It's a great idea, Nancy.

17:04.000 --> 17:06.000
Yes, I'm very sure.

17:06.000 --> 17:09.000
You and Josie can visit me any time.

17:09.000 --> 17:11.000
It is nearby.

17:11.000 --> 17:12.000
There we are.

17:12.000 --> 17:14.000
Everyone is happy.

17:14.000 --> 17:16.000
Pass a biscuit, Josie.

17:16.000 --> 17:17.000
Thanks.

17:17.000 --> 17:19.000
Can't sit here doing nothing.

17:19.000 --> 17:23.000
Daddy is horrible to you, Grand.

17:23.000 --> 17:25.000
Why doesn't he like you?

17:25.000 --> 17:27.000
A good question, Josie.

17:27.000 --> 17:30.000
Does he like anyone on the planet?

17:30.000 --> 17:32.000
Only himself.

17:38.000 --> 17:40.000
Wake up, Pete.

17:42.000 --> 17:43.000
What?

17:43.000 --> 17:46.000
Well, not now, Naomi.

17:46.000 --> 17:49.000
Oh, it's you, Nancy.

17:49.000 --> 17:51.000
Yes, it's Nancy.

17:51.000 --> 17:52.000
Your wife, remember?

17:52.000 --> 17:54.000
Yes, of course, Nancy.

17:54.000 --> 17:56.000
Why did you wake me up?

17:56.000 --> 17:58.000
Because...

17:58.000 --> 18:00.000
Who's Naomi?

18:00.000 --> 18:01.000
Who?

18:01.000 --> 18:03.000
What do you mean, who's Naomi?

18:03.000 --> 18:06.000
You said not now, Naomi, when I woke you up.

18:06.000 --> 18:07.000
I'm sure I didn't.

18:07.000 --> 18:08.000
You did it.

18:08.000 --> 18:10.000
Where did you think I was?

18:10.000 --> 18:13.000
I was dreaming of Naomi Campbell.

18:13.000 --> 18:15.000
Are you sure?

18:15.000 --> 18:18.000
If not, we can talk about this later.

18:18.000 --> 18:20.000
Come on, get out of bed.

18:20.000 --> 18:22.000
It's Saturday.

18:22.000 --> 18:24.000
I always get up late.

18:25.000 --> 18:27.000
It's only half past nine.

18:27.000 --> 18:28.000
Don't argue.

18:28.000 --> 18:29.000
Get up.

18:29.000 --> 18:30.000
It's Mum.

18:30.000 --> 18:31.000
What?

18:31.000 --> 18:33.000
Did you pop a clog in the night?

18:33.000 --> 18:35.000
No, I'm pleased to say.

18:35.000 --> 18:37.000
Come on, hurry up.

18:37.000 --> 18:39.000
I'm going downstairs.

18:39.000 --> 18:41.000
They want all of us.

18:41.000 --> 18:42.000
What do you mean?

18:42.000 --> 18:44.000
They want all of us.

18:44.000 --> 18:48.000
I suppose I have to get up.

18:48.000 --> 18:51.000
Can you wait until tonight, Naomi?

18:51.000 --> 18:53.000
I'm coming, I'm coming!

18:53.000 --> 18:55.000
Just waiting in the kitchen, Mum.

18:55.000 --> 18:57.000
Josie, Pete's on his way.

18:57.000 --> 18:59.000
This is so exciting.

18:59.000 --> 19:01.000
I think I need to go to the toilet.

19:01.000 --> 19:03.000
Do they want me in the photograph as well?

19:03.000 --> 19:05.000
Yes, the whole family.

19:05.000 --> 19:06.000
And Boris.

19:06.000 --> 19:07.000
And Robbie.

19:07.000 --> 19:08.000
Oh.

19:08.000 --> 19:09.000
Robbie?

19:09.000 --> 19:12.000
Your father told you to sell that rat.

19:12.000 --> 19:13.000
Oh.

19:13.000 --> 19:14.000
Well.

19:14.000 --> 19:15.000
No.

19:15.000 --> 19:18.000
I forgot to tell you, Mum.

19:18.000 --> 19:20.000
I forgot to tell you.

19:20.000 --> 19:22.000
Don't worry.

19:22.000 --> 19:25.000
You know he's very quiet and clean and he can stay in my room.

19:25.000 --> 19:27.000
But I told you to.

19:27.000 --> 19:28.000
But his house trained.

19:28.000 --> 19:29.000
He's so nice.

19:29.000 --> 19:31.000
Yes, I know.

19:31.000 --> 19:34.000
He is quite sweet, but what about your father?

19:34.000 --> 19:37.000
I'm sure you can think of something to say to him.

19:37.000 --> 19:39.000
Please don't tell him.

19:39.000 --> 19:42.000
I have to think of something to say to him.

19:42.000 --> 19:43.000
Children.

19:43.000 --> 19:44.000
What a life.

19:44.000 --> 19:45.000
Okay.

19:45.000 --> 19:47.000
Just keep quiet.

19:47.000 --> 19:48.000
Leave it to me.

19:48.000 --> 19:49.000
Thanks, Mum.

19:49.000 --> 19:52.000
What are the strange people in our living room on a Saturday morning?

19:52.000 --> 19:54.000
You still have your pajamas on?

19:54.000 --> 19:55.000
Yes.

19:55.000 --> 19:58.000
I didn't expect to find my house full of people.

19:58.000 --> 19:59.000
What's happening?

19:59.000 --> 20:01.000
Oh, mega embarrassing.

20:01.000 --> 20:04.000
Why are you wearing those pajamas on?

20:04.000 --> 20:05.000
I don't know.

20:05.000 --> 20:06.000
I don't know.

20:06.000 --> 20:07.000
I don't know.

20:07.000 --> 20:08.000
I don't know.

20:08.000 --> 20:09.000
I don't know.

20:09.000 --> 20:10.000
I don't know.

20:10.000 --> 20:11.000
I don't know.

20:11.000 --> 20:12.000
I don't know.

20:12.000 --> 20:13.000
I don't know.

20:13.000 --> 20:15.000
Why are you wearing those pajamas?

20:15.000 --> 20:16.000
I bought them.

20:16.000 --> 20:17.000
What's wrong with them?

20:17.000 --> 20:19.000
I like Winnie the Pooh.

20:19.000 --> 20:21.000
Ticker is my favourite.

20:21.000 --> 20:22.000
He's always so good.

20:22.000 --> 20:24.000
Can we all stop discussing my pajamas?

20:24.000 --> 20:26.000
There's nothing about tickeries.

20:26.000 --> 20:27.000
Be quiet.

20:27.000 --> 20:30.000
What's the matter with everyone this morning?

20:30.000 --> 20:32.000
Why are they sitting on our lounge?

20:32.000 --> 20:33.000
Because of Mum.

20:33.000 --> 20:34.000
What did she do?

20:34.000 --> 20:36.000
Win the Nobel Prize for physics.

20:36.000 --> 20:37.000
No, Pete.

20:37.000 --> 20:40.000
She's our new special envoy at the United Nations.

20:40.000 --> 20:42.000
Don't we say nasty, Pete?

20:42.000 --> 20:43.000
No.

20:43.000 --> 20:46.000
Mum won a competition at Tesco's.

20:46.000 --> 20:48.000
A year supply of baked beans.

20:48.000 --> 20:50.000
No, something much more exciting.

20:50.000 --> 20:51.000
A lifetime supply.

20:51.000 --> 20:52.000
A toilet paper.

20:52.000 --> 20:54.000
No, Pete.

20:54.000 --> 20:57.000
Mum won a house.

20:57.000 --> 20:58.000
A house?

20:58.000 --> 21:00.000
A house?

21:00.000 --> 21:02.000
A what?

21:02.000 --> 21:03.000
For Boris?

21:03.000 --> 21:04.000
No.

21:04.000 --> 21:07.000
You do know what a house is, don't you?

21:07.000 --> 21:09.000
Of course I do, but...

21:09.000 --> 21:10.000
I don't understand.

21:10.000 --> 21:14.000
Mum entered a competition at the supermarket last month.

21:14.000 --> 21:19.000
She had to guess how many jars of Marmite was sold in Britain every week.

21:19.000 --> 21:24.000
The prize for the nearest guess was a new detached house.

21:24.000 --> 21:25.000
She won it.

21:25.000 --> 21:26.000
I won it.

21:26.000 --> 21:27.000
I won it.

21:27.000 --> 21:34.000
I had no idea what the answer was, so I wrote down the first number that came into my head.

21:34.000 --> 21:37.000
63,360.

21:37.000 --> 21:40.000
I remember it from my primary school days.

21:40.000 --> 21:42.000
Amazing.

21:42.000 --> 21:44.000
Absolutely amazing.

21:44.000 --> 21:47.000
Why 63,360 grand?

21:47.000 --> 21:50.000
It's the number of inches in a mile.

21:50.000 --> 21:52.000
Amazing.

21:52.000 --> 21:54.000
Absolutely amazing.

21:54.000 --> 21:56.000
Your cool grand.

21:56.000 --> 21:57.000
Awesome.

21:57.000 --> 21:59.000
And the people in our lounge?

21:59.000 --> 22:04.000
It's the local photographer from the newspaper and someone from the supermarket.

22:04.000 --> 22:08.000
They want to take our photo and give us the key to the house.

22:08.000 --> 22:10.000
Does this mean we can all live together?

22:10.000 --> 22:12.000
We don't have to move into a flat.

22:12.000 --> 22:14.000
Yes, that's right.

22:14.000 --> 22:17.000
Is that all right with you, Pete?

22:17.000 --> 22:19.000
Yes, I suppose so.

22:19.000 --> 22:20.000
Awesome.

22:20.000 --> 22:21.000
Come on, let's go.

22:21.000 --> 22:22.000
I'm coming.

22:22.000 --> 22:26.000
It is my hair all right, Josie.

22:26.000 --> 22:30.000
We're one big happy family again.

22:30.000 --> 22:34.000
I'm so happy we can go on living with your mother.

22:34.000 --> 22:37.000
We must be very grateful to her.

22:37.000 --> 22:39.000
That's the problem.

22:52.000 --> 22:55.000
It's a lovely house, Pete.

22:55.000 --> 22:57.000
I went to look at it this morning.

22:57.000 --> 23:00.000
It's ready and we can move in when we want.

23:00.000 --> 23:03.000
It's more modern than this house.

23:03.000 --> 23:05.000
The bathroom's a wonderful.

23:05.000 --> 23:07.000
The kitchen is wonderful.

23:07.000 --> 23:09.000
Everything is wonderful.

23:09.000 --> 23:11.000
The garden is wonderful.

23:11.000 --> 23:13.000
Yes, yes, I get the picture.

23:13.000 --> 23:15.000
Can you organise a removal firm?

23:15.000 --> 23:18.000
There are lots of advertisements in the yellow pages.

23:18.000 --> 23:19.000
Leave it to me.

23:19.000 --> 23:21.000
I have a friend at work who knows a firm.

23:21.000 --> 23:22.000
I hope they're good.

23:22.000 --> 23:23.000
Yes, yes.

23:23.000 --> 23:24.000
Don't worry.

23:24.000 --> 23:27.000
You are happy to move into this house with Mum, aren't you, Pete?

23:27.000 --> 23:28.000
Yes, dear.

23:28.000 --> 23:33.000
I mean, we have to move because of your job and this is the best alternative.

23:33.000 --> 23:34.000
Yes, dear.

23:34.000 --> 23:36.000
I know you're right.

23:36.000 --> 23:39.000
And this house is looking so shabby.

23:39.000 --> 23:41.000
What do you mean?

23:41.000 --> 23:42.000
Let's start.

23:42.000 --> 23:44.000
Just look at this wallpaper here in the dining room.

23:44.000 --> 23:45.000
I like it.

23:45.000 --> 23:47.000
No, you don't.

23:47.000 --> 23:49.000
It's 23 years old.

23:49.000 --> 23:51.000
You just don't like doing DIY.

23:51.000 --> 23:53.000
I don't mind DIY.

23:53.000 --> 23:56.000
When was the last time you did anything in this house?

23:56.000 --> 23:57.000
Um...

23:57.000 --> 23:59.000
Can you see?

23:59.000 --> 24:00.000
I'm right.

24:00.000 --> 24:01.000
No, wait.

24:01.000 --> 24:04.000
I changed the light bulb in the kitchen last month.

24:04.000 --> 24:06.000
Need I say any more?

24:06.000 --> 24:08.000
Anyway, can we stop arguing?

24:08.000 --> 24:09.000
We're not arguing.

24:09.000 --> 24:10.000
Yes, we are.

24:10.000 --> 24:11.000
No, wait.

24:11.000 --> 24:12.000
This is stupid.

24:12.000 --> 24:13.000
I agree.

24:13.000 --> 24:14.000
Come on.

24:14.000 --> 24:17.000
We said we wanted to start for sorting out today.

24:17.000 --> 24:18.000
Okay.

24:18.000 --> 24:21.000
We can start with this cupboard of stuff.

24:21.000 --> 24:23.000
Do you never use any of it?

24:23.000 --> 24:24.000
Look, these for a start.

24:24.000 --> 24:25.000
No.

24:25.000 --> 24:26.000
Don't throw them out.

24:26.000 --> 24:27.000
Why not?

24:27.000 --> 24:28.000
They are old.

24:28.000 --> 24:29.000
We never use them.

24:29.000 --> 24:31.000
They might be useful one day.

24:31.000 --> 24:33.000
What use are six?

24:33.000 --> 24:34.000
Six?

24:34.000 --> 24:35.000
Salt and pepper pot.

24:35.000 --> 24:38.000
Perhaps we have visitors in the new house.

24:38.000 --> 24:39.000
Visitors?

24:39.000 --> 24:41.000
How many are you expecting?

24:41.000 --> 24:44.000
The entire Hampshire cricket team and their wives.

24:44.000 --> 24:45.000
And the crowd.

24:45.000 --> 24:47.000
There's no need to be like that, Pete.

24:47.000 --> 24:50.000
I just don't like to throw things away.

24:50.000 --> 24:53.000
But we said we were going to throw things out.

24:53.000 --> 24:56.000
We have too much stuff and we don't need it all in the new house.

24:56.000 --> 24:57.000
I know.

24:57.000 --> 24:59.000
But it's so difficult.

24:59.000 --> 25:01.000
What have we put in the box for the car boot sale?

25:01.000 --> 25:02.000
Let me look.

25:05.000 --> 25:06.000
A broken egg cup.

25:06.000 --> 25:09.000
Two tea towels from Mallorca.

25:09.000 --> 25:12.000
A frying pan with no handle and...

25:13.000 --> 25:14.000
Aah!

25:14.000 --> 25:16.000
Cuckoo clock with only one hand.

25:16.000 --> 25:18.000
Not very impressive for three hours work, is it?

25:18.000 --> 25:19.000
No, it isn't.

25:19.000 --> 25:20.000
Okay.

25:20.000 --> 25:23.000
We must try to be more ruthless.

25:23.000 --> 25:25.000
What do you mean we?

25:25.000 --> 25:26.000
Yes, I know.

25:26.000 --> 25:27.000
All right, Pete.

25:27.000 --> 25:28.000
Good.

25:28.000 --> 25:30.000
Now what is this?

25:30.000 --> 25:32.000
A back of the cupboard.

25:32.000 --> 25:33.000
Give it to me.

25:33.000 --> 25:37.000
It's still in its original box.

25:37.000 --> 25:40.000
It can't be important, surely.

25:40.000 --> 25:43.000
It's a pasta machine for making fresh pasta.

25:43.000 --> 25:47.000
You don't like pasta, so it can definitely go to the car boot sale.

25:47.000 --> 25:49.000
But wait a minute, Pete.

25:49.000 --> 25:51.000
Now we don't need it.

25:51.000 --> 25:55.000
I just want to look at it for a moment.

25:55.000 --> 25:57.000
Okay now?

25:57.000 --> 25:58.000
Yes.

25:58.000 --> 25:59.000
You're right.

25:59.000 --> 26:01.000
We don't need it.

26:01.000 --> 26:03.000
Into the car boot box.

26:03.000 --> 26:06.000
Might get five pounds for that.

26:06.000 --> 26:09.000
You know it was a wedding present, Pete.

26:09.000 --> 26:10.000
Really?

26:10.000 --> 26:14.000
Another useless present, a complete waste of money.

26:14.000 --> 26:16.000
The things people buy.

26:17.000 --> 26:20.000
Why didn't we write a wedding list for everyone to choose from?

26:20.000 --> 26:23.000
Because you said it's more fun to see what people buy us.

26:23.000 --> 26:24.000
Did I?

26:24.000 --> 26:25.000
I don't remember.

26:25.000 --> 26:27.000
Anyway, into the car boot box.

26:27.000 --> 26:30.000
What a load of rubbish.

26:30.000 --> 26:33.000
You know that it was a present from your parents.

26:33.000 --> 26:34.000
What?

26:34.000 --> 26:36.000
The pasta machine.

26:36.000 --> 26:37.000
Are you sure?

26:37.000 --> 26:38.000
Yes.

26:38.000 --> 26:40.000
Look closely at the side of the box.

26:40.000 --> 26:42.000
You can see they wrote their names.

26:42.000 --> 26:43.000
Let me look.

26:43.000 --> 26:45.000
You're right.

26:45.000 --> 26:48.000
We can't throw this out, can we?

26:48.000 --> 26:51.000
Might be useful one day, Nancy.

26:51.000 --> 26:52.000
But you said...

26:52.000 --> 26:54.000
No, it's from my parents, dear.

26:54.000 --> 26:55.000
Right.

26:55.000 --> 26:56.000
What's next?

26:56.000 --> 26:59.000
What's in these drawers?

26:59.000 --> 27:03.000
Interesting.

27:03.000 --> 27:05.000
I didn't know you were a member of Appa.

27:05.000 --> 27:07.000
Are you talking about...

27:07.000 --> 27:09.000
Oh, this photo.

27:09.000 --> 27:11.000
What are you wearing?

27:11.000 --> 27:12.000
It was fashionable then.

27:12.000 --> 27:14.000
Everyone was wearing those skirts.

27:14.000 --> 27:16.000
What did you do with it?

27:16.000 --> 27:18.000
I would love to see you in it now.

27:18.000 --> 27:20.000
Don't get up stairs.

27:20.000 --> 27:22.000
Let me go and look.

27:22.000 --> 27:23.000
It's okay.

27:23.000 --> 27:25.000
I was only joking.

27:27.000 --> 27:29.000
What do you think, Boris?

27:29.000 --> 27:33.000
Prepare yourself for a shock, Nancy, in a mini skirt.

27:33.000 --> 27:36.000
I must try not to laugh too much.

27:36.000 --> 27:39.000
You keep quiet too, Boris.

27:39.000 --> 27:41.000
Here she comes.

27:41.000 --> 27:43.000
Now remember, Boris, don't start laughing.

27:43.000 --> 27:45.000
Here I am.

27:45.000 --> 27:47.000
What do you think?

27:47.000 --> 27:51.000
I think it shrunk in the wardrobe.

27:51.000 --> 27:53.000
Well?

27:53.000 --> 27:57.000
Well, say something.

27:57.000 --> 27:59.000
It's...

27:59.000 --> 28:01.000
It's...

28:01.000 --> 28:03.000
So you think it's funny, do you?

28:03.000 --> 28:05.000
No, it's...

28:05.000 --> 28:06.000
It's...

28:06.000 --> 28:07.000
It's...

28:07.000 --> 28:09.000
It's interesting, dear.

28:09.000 --> 28:11.000
Is that all you can say?

28:11.000 --> 28:13.000
No, no, no. It's...

28:13.000 --> 28:15.000
Interesting and...

28:15.000 --> 28:18.000
Very interesting, dear.

28:18.000 --> 28:20.000
I want to keep it on.

28:20.000 --> 28:22.000
It reminds me of Happy Days.

28:22.000 --> 28:24.000
Yes, you do that, dear.

28:24.000 --> 28:29.000
I need to go outside to wash the flowers.

28:29.000 --> 28:30.000
No.

28:30.000 --> 28:31.000
What's the car?

28:31.000 --> 28:32.000
No.

28:32.000 --> 28:34.000
Back in a minute, dear.

28:35.000 --> 28:43.000
We're moving at the weekend, Pete.

28:43.000 --> 28:45.000
Please come and help me.

28:45.000 --> 28:46.000
Where are you?

28:46.000 --> 28:48.000
I'm in the loft.

28:48.000 --> 28:51.000
There are so many boxes here.

28:51.000 --> 28:53.000
What's in them?

28:53.000 --> 28:54.000
Which boxes?

28:54.000 --> 28:56.000
Oh, those are my things.

28:56.000 --> 28:57.000
Don't throw them out.

28:57.000 --> 28:59.000
They're old things for my school days.

28:59.000 --> 29:01.000
I want to look at them.

29:01.000 --> 29:02.000
Oh, do we really have to?

29:02.000 --> 29:04.000
I want to look at them.

29:04.000 --> 29:07.000
See if you were a good pupil at school.

29:07.000 --> 29:09.000
Okay, here you are.

29:09.000 --> 29:11.000
What's this?

29:11.000 --> 29:14.000
Oh, how sweet.

29:14.000 --> 29:17.000
It's your first writing book from primary school.

29:17.000 --> 29:19.000
It's embarrassing, Nancy.

29:19.000 --> 29:20.000
No, it's sweet.

29:20.000 --> 29:22.000
Look what you wrote.

29:22.000 --> 29:24.000
My name is Peter.

29:24.000 --> 29:25.000
I have a mother.

29:25.000 --> 29:26.000
She cooks.

29:26.000 --> 29:28.000
I have a father.

29:28.000 --> 29:30.000
He sleeps on the sofa.

29:31.000 --> 29:33.000
Yes, he did.

29:33.000 --> 29:34.000
And look here.

29:34.000 --> 29:37.000
There's a picture of you in a swimming costume.

29:37.000 --> 29:38.000
How sexy.

29:38.000 --> 29:40.000
No, I look terrible.

29:40.000 --> 29:43.000
I think that was the first time we went to blackpool.

29:43.000 --> 29:46.000
I was six years old.

29:46.000 --> 29:48.000
What's this?

29:48.000 --> 29:50.000
I don't believe it.

29:50.000 --> 29:52.000
It's my old school uniform.

29:52.000 --> 29:53.000
On an awful colour.

29:53.000 --> 29:55.000
Did I really have to wear that to school?

29:55.000 --> 29:59.000
Oh, dark blue and pink stripes is very fashionable these days.

29:59.000 --> 30:00.000
Please, try it on.

30:00.000 --> 30:02.000
I want to see what it looks like.

30:02.000 --> 30:03.000
No, I'm not.

30:03.000 --> 30:04.000
It's too small.

30:04.000 --> 30:05.000
Oh, please.

30:05.000 --> 30:06.000
Just for me.

30:06.000 --> 30:07.000
Come on.

30:07.000 --> 30:08.000
I can help you.

30:08.000 --> 30:09.000
I don't want to.

30:09.000 --> 30:10.000
Oh, don't be so stupid.

30:10.000 --> 30:11.000
Come on.

30:11.000 --> 30:12.000
No!

30:12.000 --> 30:13.000
Get off, Nancy!

30:13.000 --> 30:14.000
Ah!

30:14.000 --> 30:15.000
Oh!

30:15.000 --> 30:16.000
Oh!

30:16.000 --> 30:17.000
Oh!

30:17.000 --> 30:18.000
My leg!

30:18.000 --> 30:19.000
Where am I?

30:19.000 --> 30:20.000
Oh!

30:20.000 --> 30:21.000
Oh, no!

30:21.000 --> 30:23.000
There's a toddler in my room.

30:23.000 --> 30:25.000
He's coming through my ceiling.

30:25.000 --> 30:26.000
No!

30:26.000 --> 30:27.000
Oh!

30:27.000 --> 30:28.000
My leg!

30:28.000 --> 30:29.000
Oh!

30:29.000 --> 30:30.000
Oh!

30:30.000 --> 30:31.000
Oh!

30:31.000 --> 30:32.000
Oh!

30:32.000 --> 30:34.000
Stop it, you stupid!

30:34.000 --> 30:35.000
Stop it!

30:35.000 --> 30:36.000
Stop it!

30:36.000 --> 30:37.000
Stop it!

30:37.000 --> 30:38.000
It's Pete!

30:38.000 --> 30:39.000
Oh!

30:39.000 --> 30:41.000
Don't worry, he's not dangerous.

30:41.000 --> 30:43.000
Just stupid.

30:43.000 --> 30:46.000
Is that you, Pete?

30:46.000 --> 30:47.000
Yes it is.

30:47.000 --> 30:48.000
Who else do you think it is?

30:48.000 --> 30:50.000
My foot hurts.

30:50.000 --> 30:53.000
Why is your foot through my ceiling?

30:53.000 --> 30:55.000
You know I have a weak heart.

30:55.000 --> 30:57.000
I almost died of fright.

30:57.000 --> 31:00.000
I always put my foot through the ceiling.

31:00.000 --> 31:02.000
It's a hobby of mine.

31:02.000 --> 31:03.000
What?

31:03.000 --> 31:05.000
What did you hit it with?

31:05.000 --> 31:07.000
I thought you were a burglar.

31:07.000 --> 31:09.000
I hit it with a bedside lamp.

31:09.000 --> 31:11.000
I think it's broken.

31:11.000 --> 31:12.000
I don't care about your lamp.

31:12.000 --> 31:14.000
I think my foot is broken.

31:14.000 --> 31:16.000
Help me, Nancy.

31:16.000 --> 31:17.000
Oh!

31:17.000 --> 31:18.000
Be careful!

31:18.000 --> 31:19.000
Oh!

31:19.000 --> 31:20.000
Don't be stupid.

31:20.000 --> 31:21.000
You can stand up.

31:21.000 --> 31:22.000
Come on.

31:22.000 --> 31:23.000
I can't.

31:23.000 --> 31:25.000
You just want some sympathy.

31:25.000 --> 31:26.000
I can't stand up.

31:26.000 --> 31:27.000
Oh!

31:27.000 --> 31:28.000
Oh!

31:28.000 --> 31:29.000
Oh!

31:29.000 --> 31:30.000
Oh!

31:30.000 --> 31:32.000
Perhaps you can't stand.

31:32.000 --> 31:34.000
Come on, Pete.

31:34.000 --> 31:36.000
Put your arm around my shoulder.

31:36.000 --> 31:38.000
Let me carry you to the bed.

31:38.000 --> 31:39.000
Oh, my God.

31:39.000 --> 31:40.000
Don't be so silly.

31:40.000 --> 31:41.000
Let me look.

31:41.000 --> 31:42.000
Oh.

31:42.000 --> 31:44.000
Oh, it's only sprained.

31:44.000 --> 31:46.000
There are lots of bruises.

31:46.000 --> 31:49.000
That's because your mother hit it with her lamp.

31:49.000 --> 31:50.000
She's very brave.

31:50.000 --> 31:51.000
Brave?

31:51.000 --> 31:53.000
She's dangerous.

31:53.000 --> 31:55.000
Send her away to any war zone.

31:55.000 --> 31:57.000
She could sort it out.

31:57.000 --> 31:59.000
Britain's answer to Mambo.

31:59.000 --> 32:01.000
She is 72 years old.

32:01.000 --> 32:02.000
Hey, Mambo.

32:02.000 --> 32:05.000
How about a week in the Middle East if they need your help?

32:05.000 --> 32:07.000
I think you're suffering from shock.

32:07.000 --> 32:08.000
Oh.

32:08.000 --> 32:09.000
Here's some aspirin.

32:09.000 --> 32:10.000
Try to rest for a few hours.

32:10.000 --> 32:13.000
I can finish looking in the boxes in the attic.

32:13.000 --> 32:14.000
I can help.

32:14.000 --> 32:16.000
Oh, it's okay.

32:16.000 --> 32:18.000
I want to...

32:18.000 --> 32:20.000
Oh.

32:20.000 --> 32:21.000
Oh.

32:21.000 --> 32:22.000
Oh.

32:22.000 --> 32:38.000
The

32:38.000 --> 32:40.000
removal van is here.

32:40.000 --> 32:41.000
Okay.

32:41.000 --> 32:42.000
Is everything ready?

32:42.000 --> 32:43.000
Where's Pete?

32:43.000 --> 32:44.000
I'm ready.

32:44.000 --> 32:47.000
Oh, this is so exciting.

32:47.000 --> 32:50.000
Our new house and our new life.

32:50.000 --> 32:52.000
Where's Pete?

33:00.000 --> 33:01.000
Good morning.

33:01.000 --> 33:02.000
Come in.

33:02.000 --> 33:03.000
Good morning.

33:03.000 --> 33:04.000
Thank you.

33:04.000 --> 33:05.000
Come on, Jim.

33:05.000 --> 33:06.000
In we go.

33:07.000 --> 33:09.000
There are only two of you.

33:09.000 --> 33:10.000
Is that enough?

33:10.000 --> 33:12.000
Jim and I always work together.

33:12.000 --> 33:14.000
No problem, madam.

33:14.000 --> 33:15.000
He may be over 65,

33:15.000 --> 33:17.000
but he can carry us over.

33:17.000 --> 33:19.000
No problem.

33:19.000 --> 33:21.000
Where do you want to start?

33:21.000 --> 33:24.000
Maybe a cup of tea before we start.

33:24.000 --> 33:27.000
It's a long day and we're both thirsty.

33:27.000 --> 33:30.000
Er, yes, I suppose that's all right.

33:30.000 --> 33:32.000
Come into the kitchen.

33:32.000 --> 33:35.000
Perhaps you have a packet of biscuits as well.

33:35.000 --> 33:38.000
A bit of toast and marmalade would be very nice.

33:38.000 --> 33:40.000
All right.

33:40.000 --> 33:42.000
Sit down if you can find a chair.

33:42.000 --> 33:45.000
Everything is packed and ready for the move.

33:45.000 --> 33:46.000
We're okay.

33:46.000 --> 33:48.000
Don't worry about us.

33:48.000 --> 33:50.000
Oh, my back.

33:50.000 --> 33:53.000
Bit of a problem with my back, but it's okay.

33:53.000 --> 33:56.000
No problem, no problem.

33:56.000 --> 33:59.000
I'm in the living room if you want me.

33:59.000 --> 34:00.000
Don't worry.

34:00.000 --> 34:02.000
We can start in a few minutes.

34:02.000 --> 34:04.000
Come here, doggy.

34:04.000 --> 34:06.000
Would you like a biscuit?

34:14.000 --> 34:15.000
Where's Pete?

34:15.000 --> 34:17.000
Why didn't you organise a proper removal company?

34:17.000 --> 34:20.000
The two of them are sitting in the kitchen eating breakfast.

34:20.000 --> 34:22.000
I think they were the cheapest.

34:22.000 --> 34:25.000
Why didn't I organise it myself?

34:25.000 --> 34:28.000
I can't get Pete to do anything.

34:28.000 --> 34:30.000
Where is he?

34:30.000 --> 34:31.000
Pete!

34:31.000 --> 34:33.000
Oh, I must go and find him.

34:33.000 --> 34:34.000
You stay here, mother.

34:34.000 --> 34:36.000
Okay, Nancy.

34:40.000 --> 34:41.000
Here I am.

34:41.000 --> 34:42.000
What is happening?

34:42.000 --> 34:44.000
Good morning, sir.

34:44.000 --> 34:45.000
Nice dog.

34:45.000 --> 34:46.000
Hello, Pete.

34:46.000 --> 34:50.000
But why are you all sitting here eating?

34:50.000 --> 34:52.000
Don't feed Boris, please.

34:52.000 --> 34:54.000
I know, George.

34:54.000 --> 34:56.000
Is it my bingo club?

34:56.000 --> 34:59.000
We have a great time together, don't we, George?

34:59.000 --> 35:02.000
We certainly do, dear.

35:02.000 --> 35:05.000
Something happened to your legs, sir.

35:05.000 --> 35:06.000
It doesn't look good.

35:06.000 --> 35:07.000
Don't ask.

35:07.000 --> 35:09.000
But that's not important at the moment.

35:09.000 --> 35:13.000
I paid a lot of money to have you move us to our new house.

35:13.000 --> 35:16.000
I did not pay for you to eat our food.

35:16.000 --> 35:20.000
And stop giving Boris my favourite biscuits.

35:20.000 --> 35:22.000
Don't be so unfriendly.

35:22.000 --> 35:24.000
I am not unfriendly.

35:24.000 --> 35:27.000
I just want these men to start work.

35:27.000 --> 35:28.000
Okay.

35:28.000 --> 35:30.000
We understand.

35:30.000 --> 35:32.000
Come on, Jim.

35:38.000 --> 35:39.000
Oh.

35:39.000 --> 35:40.000
There you are.

35:40.000 --> 35:42.000
What did you say to the removal men?

35:42.000 --> 35:44.000
They look very unhappy.

35:44.000 --> 35:48.000
Typical workers, sitting, drinking tea and eating biscuits.

35:48.000 --> 35:50.000
I just told them to start work.

35:50.000 --> 35:52.000
He was very unfriendly.

35:52.000 --> 35:54.000
They are very nice men.

35:54.000 --> 35:57.000
Why do you always upset people?

35:57.000 --> 35:59.000
And why did you choose that company?

35:59.000 --> 36:00.000
They were the cheapest.

36:00.000 --> 36:02.000
I can see why they were the cheapest.

36:02.000 --> 36:04.000
Both of them look older than my mum.

36:04.000 --> 36:07.000
I'm sure they know what they are doing.

36:10.000 --> 36:12.000
What was that?

36:12.000 --> 36:14.000
I didn't hear anything.

36:14.000 --> 36:16.000
What are you doing now, Pete?

36:16.000 --> 36:20.000
Sitting and having a cup of tea and perhaps a couple of biscuits.

36:20.000 --> 36:21.000
If there are any left.

36:21.000 --> 36:23.000
I don't believe it.

36:23.000 --> 36:25.000
Come on, mum.

36:25.000 --> 36:28.000
Sorry about the words, madam.

36:28.000 --> 36:31.000
My eyesight's not as good as it used to be.

36:31.000 --> 36:33.000
Got a bit of a shock.

36:33.000 --> 36:35.000
Thought I saw a rat.

36:35.000 --> 36:37.000
But I...

36:37.000 --> 36:40.000
Josie, we don't have rats in this house.

36:40.000 --> 36:44.000
Don't worry, a bit of glue is all it needs.

36:44.000 --> 36:49.000
But perhaps you and your mother could help us carry these boxes.

36:49.000 --> 36:52.000
They're a bit too heavy for the two of us.

36:52.000 --> 36:55.000
Yes, I always wanted to pick you up.

36:55.000 --> 36:59.000
You can pick me up any time, love.

36:59.000 --> 37:00.000
Come on, Nancy.

37:00.000 --> 37:02.000
You stand in that corner.

37:02.000 --> 37:06.000
One, two, three, lift!

37:12.000 --> 37:15.000
Why did you choose that removal firm?

37:15.000 --> 37:17.000
Don't keep asking the same question.

37:17.000 --> 37:20.000
I know the answer, because they were the cheapest.

37:20.000 --> 37:22.000
Yes, they were the cheapest.

37:22.000 --> 37:24.000
How many more times do I have to tell you?

37:24.000 --> 37:26.000
But where are they?

37:26.000 --> 37:27.000
Be patient.

37:27.000 --> 37:29.000
Be patient.

37:29.000 --> 37:31.000
How long does it take to drive 15 miles?

37:31.000 --> 37:33.000
Well, well.

37:33.000 --> 37:35.000
Well, yes.

37:35.000 --> 37:37.000
Four hours is quite a long time.

37:37.000 --> 37:39.000
It's getting dark, Pete.

37:39.000 --> 37:41.000
I can see it's getting dark.

37:41.000 --> 37:42.000
And cold.

37:42.000 --> 37:43.000
And I'm hungry.

37:43.000 --> 37:47.000
Yes, yes, and Boris is hungry too, I suppose.

37:47.000 --> 37:48.000
I know, I know.

37:48.000 --> 37:50.000
It's all my fault.

37:50.000 --> 37:52.000
We all make mistakes.

37:54.000 --> 37:56.000
Oh, here it comes.

37:56.000 --> 37:57.000
At night.

37:57.000 --> 37:58.000
Yes, see?

37:58.000 --> 38:02.000
You see everything is OK.

38:15.000 --> 38:17.000
We're here.

38:17.000 --> 38:19.000
I told you, Jim.

38:19.000 --> 38:20.000
Sorry about that.

38:20.000 --> 38:22.000
We got lost.

38:22.000 --> 38:23.000
We got lost.

38:23.000 --> 38:24.000
It's only 15 miles.

38:24.000 --> 38:26.000
Yes, I know.

38:26.000 --> 38:32.000
But I wrote down Mulberry Avenue and Jim wrote down Mulberry Road.

38:32.000 --> 38:36.000
So, so first we went to Mulberry Road.

38:36.000 --> 38:37.000
But why?

38:37.000 --> 38:39.000
This is Mulberry Avenue.

38:39.000 --> 38:40.000
Yes.

38:40.000 --> 38:43.000
I know that now, but I didn't before.

38:43.000 --> 38:45.000
So where is Mulberry Road?

38:45.000 --> 38:46.000
I don't know.

38:46.000 --> 38:47.000
What do you mean?

38:47.000 --> 38:48.000
You don't know.

38:48.000 --> 38:49.000
We didn't find it.

38:49.000 --> 38:51.000
There isn't a Mulberry Road.

38:51.000 --> 38:53.000
It's not on the map.

38:53.000 --> 38:56.000
So why did you look for Mulberry Road?

38:56.000 --> 38:59.000
Because Jim was sure that was where your house was.

38:59.000 --> 39:02.000
But where did you look if it's not on the map?

39:02.000 --> 39:03.000
Well, we...

39:03.000 --> 39:06.000
What happened to the roof of your van?

39:06.000 --> 39:07.000
Oh, yes.

39:07.000 --> 39:09.000
I thought you might ask about that.

39:09.000 --> 39:13.000
When we were looking for Mulberry Road...

39:13.000 --> 39:15.000
Which isn't on the map?

39:15.000 --> 39:18.000
Yes, which isn't on the map.

39:18.000 --> 39:21.000
When we were looking for Mulberry Road,

39:21.000 --> 39:24.000
we didn't see the low bridge.

39:24.000 --> 39:26.000
You hit the bridge.

39:26.000 --> 39:30.000
Yes, we hit the bridge.

39:30.000 --> 39:32.000
But only gently.

39:32.000 --> 39:34.000
Only gently.

39:34.000 --> 39:36.000
Only gently.

39:36.000 --> 39:37.000
Don't worry.

39:37.000 --> 39:39.000
We can repair the van.

39:39.000 --> 39:43.000
I am not interested in your stupid van.

39:43.000 --> 39:45.000
What about our furniture?

39:45.000 --> 39:46.000
It's all a...

39:46.000 --> 39:47.000
Don't worry.

39:47.000 --> 39:48.000
No problem.

39:48.000 --> 39:49.000
It's just...

39:49.000 --> 39:55.000
There may be a few extra pieces of furnace.

39:55.000 --> 39:57.000
What do you mean?

39:57.000 --> 40:01.000
Well, when we hit the bridge...

40:01.000 --> 40:03.000
Gently.

40:03.000 --> 40:09.000
We heard one or two things move in the back of the van.

40:09.000 --> 40:16.000
So it is possible that one or two things are not exactly in the same number of pieces.

40:16.000 --> 40:19.000
I don't believe this is happening.

40:19.000 --> 40:20.000
Don't worry.

40:20.000 --> 40:22.000
A bit of glue is all we need.

40:22.000 --> 40:25.000
So you were telling us that our furniture is in pieces?

40:25.000 --> 40:27.000
No, I'm not saying that.

40:27.000 --> 40:29.000
So what are you saying?

40:29.000 --> 40:33.000
I'm saying that there is a possibility.

40:33.000 --> 40:40.000
Only a possibility that your furniture is in more pieces now than when you bought it.

40:40.000 --> 40:41.000
What?

40:41.000 --> 40:43.000
Now listen.

40:44.000 --> 40:50.000
My family and I are going to leave you two here to move the furniture into the house.

40:50.000 --> 40:58.000
When we come back in three hours, we expect to find everything inside and you two waiting here.

40:58.000 --> 41:02.000
If everything is all right, you can have your money.

41:02.000 --> 41:03.000
Is that clear?

41:03.000 --> 41:05.000
Yes, but no problem.

41:05.000 --> 41:07.000
No problem.

41:07.000 --> 41:09.000
Can you stop saying no problem?

41:09.000 --> 41:10.000
No problem.

41:10.000 --> 41:11.000
Of course.

41:11.000 --> 41:12.000
No problem.

41:12.000 --> 41:15.000
Come on, Pete.

41:15.000 --> 41:17.000
Get in the car, everyone.

41:17.000 --> 41:20.000
Can you move your van so we can get out, please?

41:20.000 --> 41:21.000
No problem.

41:21.000 --> 41:22.000
No problem.

41:22.000 --> 41:23.000
What?

41:23.000 --> 41:25.000
Get in the car, Pete.

41:40.000 --> 41:42.000
Oh, what?

41:42.000 --> 41:47.000
They're not backwards yet.

41:47.000 --> 41:50.000
My car.

41:50.000 --> 41:59.000
What's the matter with the door?

41:59.000 --> 42:00.000
Morning.

42:00.000 --> 42:01.000
Don't sit.

42:01.000 --> 42:02.000
My leg.

42:02.000 --> 42:03.000
What happened?

42:03.000 --> 42:07.000
I tried to tell you not to sit on that chair.

42:07.000 --> 42:08.000
Why not?

42:08.000 --> 42:09.000
What?

42:09.000 --> 42:12.000
Why has this chair only got three legs?

42:12.000 --> 42:15.000
I think you know why, Pete.

42:15.000 --> 42:17.000
Another piece of broken furniture.

42:17.000 --> 42:18.000
I told you.

42:18.000 --> 42:19.000
Oh, yes.

42:19.000 --> 42:20.000
Don't.

42:20.000 --> 42:21.000
Don't.

42:21.000 --> 42:24.000
What is that noise?

42:24.000 --> 42:26.000
It's seven o'clock.

42:26.000 --> 42:27.000
Is someone cutting the grass?

42:27.000 --> 42:29.000
I think it's from next door.

42:29.000 --> 42:33.000
At this time in the morning, I'm going to tell them to stop.

42:33.000 --> 42:34.000
Be nice, dear.

42:34.000 --> 42:35.000
Don't be nasty.

42:35.000 --> 42:37.000
I am very polite.

42:37.000 --> 42:42.000
Leave it to me.

42:42.000 --> 42:44.000
All right, bad max.

42:44.000 --> 42:47.000
Could you stop, please?

42:47.000 --> 42:53.000
It's Terminator, and you'd stop, please.

42:53.000 --> 42:54.000
There's?

42:54.000 --> 42:55.000
What's the problem?

42:55.000 --> 42:56.000
Good morning.

42:56.000 --> 42:57.000
My name's Pete Britton.

42:57.000 --> 42:59.000
We are your new neighbors.

42:59.000 --> 43:00.000
Hello?

43:00.000 --> 43:01.000
Good morning.

43:01.000 --> 43:02.000
Pleasure to meet you.

43:02.000 --> 43:03.000
My name is Derek Lump.

43:03.000 --> 43:04.000
Most people call me Colonel.

43:04.000 --> 43:06.000
This is the wife, Judith.

43:06.000 --> 43:07.000
Say hello.

43:07.000 --> 43:08.000
Hello.

43:08.000 --> 43:09.000
It's very early.

43:09.000 --> 43:12.000
Do you have to cut the grass at this time?

43:12.000 --> 43:14.000
Every morning, 0700 hours, precisely.

43:14.000 --> 43:16.000
A thousand better, 0600 hours.

43:16.000 --> 43:18.000
A wife gets breakfast at 0650 hours.

43:18.000 --> 43:19.000
Don't you wife?

43:19.000 --> 43:20.000
Yes, dear.

43:20.000 --> 43:22.000
This is lost at 0645 hours.

43:22.000 --> 43:23.000
That's right, wife?

43:23.000 --> 43:24.000
Yes, dear.

43:24.000 --> 43:27.000
Cut the grass at 0700 hours to 0730 hours.

43:27.000 --> 43:29.000
Then a long walk until 0900 hours.

43:29.000 --> 43:30.000
Got to keep fit.

43:30.000 --> 43:31.000
Healthy body, healthy mind.

43:31.000 --> 43:32.000
Every day.

43:32.000 --> 43:33.000
Yes?

43:33.000 --> 43:36.000
Why don't you go for a walk first and then cut the grass?

43:36.000 --> 43:37.000
What?

43:37.000 --> 43:38.000
Can't do that.

43:38.000 --> 43:39.000
Who do you think you are?

43:39.000 --> 43:40.000
What I did?

43:40.000 --> 43:41.000
Did you hear him, wife?

43:41.000 --> 43:42.000
Yes, dear.

43:42.000 --> 43:45.000
You can't cut the grass at this time every morning.

43:45.000 --> 43:47.000
This country is falling apart,

43:47.000 --> 43:50.000
typical of the younger generation when I was younger.

43:50.000 --> 43:53.000
You can't cut the grass so early every morning.

43:53.000 --> 43:54.000
Yes, I can.

43:54.000 --> 43:56.000
I can do what I want in my own garden.

43:56.000 --> 43:58.000
No, you can't.

43:58.000 --> 43:59.000
Hello.

43:59.000 --> 44:01.000
My name is Nancy Britton.

44:01.000 --> 44:02.000
I'm Pete's wife.

44:02.000 --> 44:05.000
Oh, madam, charmed, I'm sure.

44:05.000 --> 44:06.000
My name is Derek Lump.

44:06.000 --> 44:07.000
Most people call me Colonel.

44:07.000 --> 44:08.000
This is the wife, Judith.

44:08.000 --> 44:09.000
Say hello.

44:09.000 --> 44:10.000
Hello.

44:10.000 --> 44:13.000
What's a lovely garden you have, Colonel?

44:13.000 --> 44:16.000
You must be very proud of it.

44:16.000 --> 44:17.000
Yes.

44:17.000 --> 44:18.000
We are, aren't we, wife?

44:18.000 --> 44:19.000
Yes, dear.

44:19.000 --> 44:21.000
It's very beautiful.

44:21.000 --> 44:24.000
I love the musical windmill in the middle.

44:24.000 --> 44:27.000
And you have so many garden gnomes.

44:27.000 --> 44:30.000
They're very interesting.

44:30.000 --> 44:32.000
Please do like them.

44:32.000 --> 44:34.000
We think they're very tasteful.

44:34.000 --> 44:37.000
Not everyone appreciates them, though.

44:37.000 --> 44:38.000
There are so many.

44:38.000 --> 44:40.000
Two hundred and seventy-four, to be precise.

44:40.000 --> 44:44.000
Maybe I can give you a guided tour of our garden one day.

44:44.000 --> 44:46.000
That would be lovely.

44:46.000 --> 44:48.000
Thank you, Colonel.

44:48.000 --> 44:54.000
But I just want to say how nice it is to have a wonderful and intelligent lady living next to us.

44:54.000 --> 44:55.000
Isn't it, wife?

44:55.000 --> 44:56.000
Yes, dear.

44:56.000 --> 44:57.000
You kind, Colonel.

44:57.000 --> 44:58.000
Thank you.

44:58.000 --> 44:59.000
Come on, Pete.

44:59.000 --> 45:01.000
We have lots of things to do in the house.

45:01.000 --> 45:04.000
Oh, if you want any help with DIY, I'm your man.

45:04.000 --> 45:05.000
Please, to help.

45:05.000 --> 45:07.000
That's very nice of you to offer.

45:07.000 --> 45:08.000
Thank you.

45:08.000 --> 45:10.000
Come on, Pete.

45:10.000 --> 45:11.000
Bye-bye, Colonel.

45:11.000 --> 45:12.000
Judith.

45:12.000 --> 45:13.000
Goodbye.

45:13.000 --> 45:14.000
Bye-bye.

45:14.000 --> 45:17.000
Why did you say all that?

45:17.000 --> 45:20.000
I was trying to get him to stop lawn mowing.

45:20.000 --> 45:21.000
Thanks for helping.

45:21.000 --> 45:24.000
All you can say is lovely garden.

45:24.000 --> 45:25.000
Lovely garden gnomes.

45:25.000 --> 45:27.000
They're absolutely revolting.

45:27.000 --> 45:28.000
I can't move.

45:28.000 --> 45:31.000
Of course they are revolting.

45:31.000 --> 45:34.000
I was trying to be nice to him.

45:34.000 --> 45:35.000
That's all.

45:35.000 --> 45:37.000
Your technique wasn't having much effect, was it?

45:37.000 --> 45:40.000
I think he was beginning to see my point of view.

45:40.000 --> 45:41.000
No, he wasn't.

45:41.000 --> 45:43.000
You were shouting at each other.

45:43.000 --> 45:47.000
The way to deal with the Colonel is to use charm.

45:47.000 --> 45:50.000
Something you don't have much of, Pete.

45:50.000 --> 45:52.000
I can be charming if I want to be.

45:52.000 --> 45:54.000
You really think so?

45:55.000 --> 45:56.000
Anyway, come on.

45:56.000 --> 45:58.000
Let's do some more unpacking.

45:58.000 --> 46:00.000
I can't find anything I want at the moment.

46:00.000 --> 46:03.000
Why didn't you label the boxes?

46:03.000 --> 46:04.000
I thought that was your job.

46:04.000 --> 46:05.000
No, we agreed.

46:11.000 --> 46:13.000
Where is the kettle?

46:13.000 --> 46:15.000
Does anyone know where the kettle is?

46:15.000 --> 46:17.000
No, I don't.

46:17.000 --> 46:20.000
Where are my CDs and my MP3 player?

46:20.000 --> 46:22.000
I must have them.

46:22.000 --> 46:24.000
I can't live without them.

46:24.000 --> 46:25.000
No idea, Josie.

46:25.000 --> 46:27.000
Your mother was meant to label the boxes.

46:27.000 --> 46:29.000
Don't start that again.

46:29.000 --> 46:35.000
No, I don't know where your CDs and your ND tree player is, Josie.

46:36.000 --> 46:39.000
It's called an MP3 player, Mum.

46:39.000 --> 46:41.000
You're so stupid.

46:41.000 --> 46:42.000
Don't speak to your mother like that.

46:42.000 --> 46:45.000
We can look for it together if you want.

46:45.000 --> 46:46.000
Thanks, Gran.

46:47.000 --> 46:49.000
At least someone cares about me.

46:50.000 --> 46:52.000
This plug is dead.

46:52.000 --> 46:54.000
Nothing works in this house.

46:54.000 --> 46:58.000
The electricity doesn't work properly, and the heating pipes make a very strange noise.

46:58.000 --> 47:00.000
The house is just new.

47:00.000 --> 47:03.000
It just needs a bit of love and affection.

47:03.000 --> 47:05.000
It's a disaster.

47:05.000 --> 47:08.000
But what happens when I switch on the fridge?

47:08.000 --> 47:09.000
The oven comes on.

47:09.000 --> 47:10.000
Yes.

47:10.000 --> 47:14.000
And when I switch on the kitchen light, the oven stops, and the fridge starts.

47:14.000 --> 47:16.000
One or two wires across.

47:16.000 --> 47:17.000
That's all.

47:17.000 --> 47:19.000
It's rather fun, isn't it?

47:19.000 --> 47:21.000
I'm glad you think so.

47:21.000 --> 47:24.000
Try flushing the toilet while we look out into the garden.

47:24.000 --> 47:25.000
Are you serious?

47:25.000 --> 47:26.000
What do you mean?

47:26.000 --> 47:28.000
Just do as I say.

47:28.000 --> 47:29.000
And watch.

47:29.000 --> 47:31.000
Oh, I want to do it.

47:37.000 --> 47:38.000
Oh, look!

47:38.000 --> 47:39.000
Oh, pretty.

47:39.000 --> 47:40.000
The fountain is.

47:40.000 --> 47:43.000
It may be pretty, but it's not very practical.

47:44.000 --> 47:47.000
You need a workman to come and sort out the problems.

47:47.000 --> 47:48.000
On a Sunday.

47:48.000 --> 47:49.000
No chance.

47:49.000 --> 47:50.000
I know.

47:50.000 --> 47:51.000
Our next door neighbour.

47:51.000 --> 47:52.000
We can ask him.

47:52.000 --> 47:53.000
Oh, no.

47:53.000 --> 47:54.000
Nancy.

47:54.000 --> 47:56.000
Please don't ask Lord Kitchener.

47:56.000 --> 47:57.000
Please.

47:57.000 --> 47:58.000
You're offered.

47:58.000 --> 47:59.000
I can phone him.

47:59.000 --> 48:01.000
I even found the telephone directory this morning.

48:01.000 --> 48:02.000
No.

48:02.000 --> 48:03.000
What was his name?

48:03.000 --> 48:04.000
Bump.

48:04.000 --> 48:05.000
Don't.

48:05.000 --> 48:06.000
No.

48:06.000 --> 48:07.000
Lump.

48:07.000 --> 48:08.000
Derek Lump.

48:08.000 --> 48:09.000
That's it.

48:09.000 --> 48:10.000
Here it is.

48:10.000 --> 48:11.000
No.

48:11.000 --> 48:14.000
Four, six, five, nine, nine, two, one.

48:14.000 --> 48:15.000
Give me the phone, Pete.

48:15.000 --> 48:17.000
Please don't, Nancy.

48:17.000 --> 48:21.000
Four, six, five, nine, nine, two, one.

48:26.000 --> 48:27.000
Hello?

48:27.000 --> 48:29.000
What hunglow Chinese takeaway?

48:29.000 --> 48:31.000
What is your order, please?

48:31.000 --> 48:32.000
Oh, I'm sorry.

48:32.000 --> 48:33.000
Wrong number.

48:33.000 --> 48:35.000
Let's try again.

48:35.000 --> 48:39.000
Four, six, five, nine, two, one.

48:42.000 --> 48:43.000
Hello?

48:43.000 --> 48:45.000
What hunglow Chinese takeaway?

48:45.000 --> 48:46.000
What is your order, please?

48:46.000 --> 48:47.000
Oh, no.

48:47.000 --> 48:48.000
Wrong number again.

48:48.000 --> 48:49.000
I'm sorry.

48:49.000 --> 48:51.000
Oh, very strange.

48:51.000 --> 48:53.000
The number is the right one.

48:53.000 --> 48:56.000
The telephone isn't working properly either.

48:56.000 --> 48:58.000
Unbelievable.

48:58.000 --> 48:59.000
Okay.

48:59.000 --> 49:01.000
You're right.

49:01.000 --> 49:04.000
Perhaps it's better to get in a professional firm in the morning.

49:04.000 --> 49:06.000
And I think there are mice in the house.

49:06.000 --> 49:07.000
What?

49:07.000 --> 49:08.000
I hope not.

49:08.000 --> 49:09.000
Look at my cardigan.

49:09.000 --> 49:10.000
Here.

49:10.000 --> 49:11.000
That's a hole, isn't it?

49:11.000 --> 49:12.000
It wasn't there yesterday.

49:12.000 --> 49:14.000
Well, all your clothes have holes in them.

49:14.000 --> 49:17.000
I'm always telling you to buy some new clothes.

49:17.000 --> 49:19.000
Didn't an old lady give you ten pence last week

49:19.000 --> 49:21.000
when you were sitting waiting for the bus?

49:21.000 --> 49:22.000
She thought you were a tramp.

49:22.000 --> 49:23.000
Very funny.

49:23.000 --> 49:26.000
Look here in this cupboard.

49:26.000 --> 49:29.000
And behind your chair, Nancy.

49:29.000 --> 49:30.000
Yes.

49:30.000 --> 49:32.000
They do look like mouse droppings.

49:32.000 --> 49:37.000
They're old and, er, yes, they are very old.

49:37.000 --> 49:40.000
So now you're both experts on mice, are you?

49:40.000 --> 49:42.000
You vacuumed here last night, didn't you, Nancy?

49:42.000 --> 49:43.000
Did I?

49:43.000 --> 49:45.000
I can't remember, Pete.

49:45.000 --> 49:46.000
Maybe I did.

49:46.000 --> 49:48.000
And, erm, maybe I didn't.

49:48.000 --> 49:49.000
I saw you.

49:49.000 --> 49:50.000
Did you?

49:50.000 --> 49:51.000
Then I did.

49:51.000 --> 49:53.000
Maybe it's Boris.

49:53.000 --> 49:54.000
Boris.

49:54.000 --> 49:55.000
Boris.

49:55.000 --> 49:56.000
It can't be Boris.

49:56.000 --> 49:57.000
What rubbish?

49:57.000 --> 49:59.000
Maybe, erm, maybe it's...

49:59.000 --> 50:00.000
Yes?

50:00.000 --> 50:01.000
Maybe, er...

50:01.000 --> 50:03.000
It's you, Gran.

50:03.000 --> 50:05.000
You're all completely mad.

50:05.000 --> 50:07.000
Tomorrow, I'm going to buy a mouse strap.

50:07.000 --> 50:08.000
You can't do that.

50:08.000 --> 50:09.000
Why not?

50:09.000 --> 50:11.000
Because, er, it might, er...

50:11.000 --> 50:13.000
Hurt him.

50:13.000 --> 50:14.000
It might hurt him.

50:14.000 --> 50:15.000
It might hurt him.

50:15.000 --> 50:16.000
It might hurt him.

50:16.000 --> 50:18.000
That is the idea.

50:18.000 --> 50:20.000
It might hurt him a lot.

50:20.000 --> 50:22.000
And how do you already know it's a him?

50:22.000 --> 50:23.000
She does.

50:23.000 --> 50:24.000
She doesn't.

50:24.000 --> 50:25.000
What?

50:25.000 --> 50:26.000
No, you don't.

50:26.000 --> 50:27.000
Yes, I do.

50:27.000 --> 50:28.000
What?

50:28.000 --> 50:30.000
You did sell that horrible rat, didn't you, Josie?

50:30.000 --> 50:31.000
Of course.

50:31.000 --> 50:33.000
I let her party on sale.

50:33.000 --> 50:35.000
I let her party on Saturday.

50:35.000 --> 50:36.000
Just the four of us.

50:36.000 --> 50:38.000
What are you talking about, Nancy?

50:38.000 --> 50:39.000
We're talking about...

50:39.000 --> 50:40.000
It's got fire.

50:40.000 --> 50:41.000
Oh, you're right.

50:41.000 --> 50:43.000
It's November the fifth.

50:43.000 --> 50:44.000
Lovely idea.

50:44.000 --> 50:45.000
I can buy the firework.

50:45.000 --> 50:46.000
Cool.

50:46.000 --> 50:47.000
I want to do the music.

50:47.000 --> 50:48.000
Yes, Josie.

50:48.000 --> 50:49.000
But some nice music.

50:49.000 --> 50:50.000
Cool.

50:50.000 --> 50:51.000
My music is nice.

50:51.000 --> 50:52.000
That's a matter of opinion.

50:52.000 --> 50:53.000
We can make a bonfire.

50:53.000 --> 50:55.000
Burn some of the rubbish in the garden.

50:55.000 --> 50:56.000
I like a good fire.

50:56.000 --> 50:57.000
That's my job.

50:57.000 --> 50:59.000
And I can do the food.

50:59.000 --> 51:01.000
Well, it's a good way to celebrate

51:01.000 --> 51:03.000
the first days in our new home.

51:03.000 --> 51:05.000
I hope everything works out all right.

51:05.000 --> 51:07.000
What do you mean?

51:07.000 --> 51:10.000
What can possibly go wrong?

51:14.000 --> 51:15.000
Come on, everyone.

51:15.000 --> 51:16.000
Let's go outside.

51:16.000 --> 51:17.000
It's dark now.

51:17.000 --> 51:19.000
Bring the sausages and the baked potatoes, Mum.

51:19.000 --> 51:21.000
Oh, it's so exciting.

51:21.000 --> 51:23.000
I'm coming.

51:23.000 --> 51:25.000
Turn on the patio lights, Pete.

51:25.000 --> 51:27.000
I think we can sit outside for a while.

51:27.000 --> 51:29.000
It's not too cold.

51:29.000 --> 51:30.000
Okay.

51:30.000 --> 51:32.000
I'm going to stop the bonfire.

51:32.000 --> 51:34.000
Come and help me, Boris.

51:34.000 --> 51:37.000
Here comes the music.

51:37.000 --> 51:39.000
Oh, that's nice, Josie.

51:39.000 --> 51:40.000
Well done.

51:40.000 --> 51:42.000
Where's the mulled wine, Nancy?

51:42.000 --> 51:44.000
I think I would like a small glass.

51:44.000 --> 51:45.000
Yes.

51:45.000 --> 51:46.000
It's on the table.

51:46.000 --> 51:47.000
But be careful, Mum.

51:47.000 --> 51:48.000
It's very strong.

51:48.000 --> 51:49.000
It's all right, Nancy.

51:49.000 --> 51:51.000
Only one glass.

51:52.000 --> 51:53.000
Mm.

51:53.000 --> 51:55.000
It tastes very nice.

51:55.000 --> 51:58.000
Maybe just another small one.

51:58.000 --> 52:01.000
I don't think it's very alcoholic.

52:01.000 --> 52:04.000
Only one glass, Mum.

52:04.000 --> 52:05.000
Yes, Nancy.

52:05.000 --> 52:07.000
Only one glass.

52:07.000 --> 52:08.000
Did you bring the sausages out, Mum?

52:08.000 --> 52:10.000
Yes, I put them on the table over there.

52:10.000 --> 52:11.000
No.

52:11.000 --> 52:12.000
No.

52:12.000 --> 52:13.000
No.

52:13.000 --> 52:14.000
No.

52:14.000 --> 52:15.000
No.

52:15.000 --> 52:16.000
No.

52:16.000 --> 52:17.000
No.

52:17.000 --> 52:18.000
No.

52:18.000 --> 52:19.000
No.

52:19.000 --> 52:20.000
No.

52:20.000 --> 52:21.000
No.

52:21.000 --> 52:22.000
It's just there over there.

52:22.000 --> 52:23.000
Not there now.

52:23.000 --> 52:24.000
Josie.

52:24.000 --> 52:25.000
No idea.

52:25.000 --> 52:26.000
I'm starving.

52:26.000 --> 52:27.000
Where are they?

52:27.000 --> 52:28.000
Oh, no.

52:28.000 --> 52:29.000
Look.

52:29.000 --> 52:31.000
There's half a sausage under the table.

52:31.000 --> 52:32.000
Boris?

52:32.000 --> 52:33.000
Where's Boris?

52:33.000 --> 52:35.000
He's over there with Dad.

52:35.000 --> 52:36.000
Pete.

52:36.000 --> 52:37.000
Come here.

52:37.000 --> 52:39.000
What's the matter?

52:39.000 --> 52:41.000
Look, the bonfire is burning well.

52:41.000 --> 52:43.000
Boris ate all the sausages.

52:43.000 --> 52:45.000
What can we do?

52:45.000 --> 52:46.000
I don't have anymore.

52:46.000 --> 52:47.000
Bloody hell.

52:47.000 --> 52:49.920
Well, no sausages, what a party.

52:49.920 --> 52:51.520
I know.

52:51.520 --> 52:53.160
Phone the colonel, his wife.

52:53.160 --> 52:55.280
Perhaps they can come over with some sausages.

52:55.280 --> 52:56.760
So I have to.

52:56.760 --> 52:59.320
Perhaps you can volunteer to be the guy for the bonfire.

52:59.320 --> 53:01.520
Just for him, please.

53:01.520 --> 53:03.200
We are trying to be nice to him.

53:03.200 --> 53:04.400
OK, OK.

53:04.400 --> 53:05.400
OK.

53:16.400 --> 53:17.600
Hello.

53:17.600 --> 53:19.400
What hung out to any of you?

53:19.400 --> 53:20.800
What is your order, please?

53:20.800 --> 53:21.800
What?

53:21.800 --> 53:23.800
Oh, no, there's bloody phone.

53:23.800 --> 53:25.200
Still not fixed.

53:25.200 --> 53:26.800
What is your order, please?

53:26.800 --> 53:27.400
What?

53:27.400 --> 53:29.120
No, I don't want the order.

53:29.120 --> 53:29.920
No.

53:29.920 --> 53:31.240
Wait a minute.

53:31.240 --> 53:33.080
Do you have any sausages?

53:33.080 --> 53:34.280
Slausages?

53:34.280 --> 53:35.680
What are sausages?

53:35.680 --> 53:36.920
Don't you know what sausages?

53:36.920 --> 53:38.680
I mean, sausages are.

53:38.680 --> 53:40.000
No, please, Tal.

53:40.000 --> 53:42.480
Well, they are long.

53:42.480 --> 53:43.600
Forget it.

53:43.600 --> 53:45.240
I can't be bothered to explain.

53:45.240 --> 53:47.240
Goodbye.

53:47.240 --> 53:48.320
What about country?

53:48.320 --> 53:50.040
I don't know what sausages are.

53:50.040 --> 53:51.320
Slausages.

53:51.320 --> 53:52.320
Unbelievable.

53:57.840 --> 54:00.040
Oh, I was trying to phone you.

54:00.040 --> 54:01.360
You don't have any sausages.

54:01.360 --> 54:03.400
I mean, sausages with you.

54:03.400 --> 54:05.120
No, I suppose not.

54:05.120 --> 54:06.120
Sorry.

54:06.120 --> 54:07.720
Oh, hello, Colonel.

54:07.720 --> 54:09.240
Nice to see you again.

54:09.240 --> 54:11.160
Come in, please.

54:11.160 --> 54:13.200
Go and look after the fire, Pete.

54:13.200 --> 54:16.160
You're having a bonfire party, I see.

54:16.160 --> 54:17.840
Yes, we are.

54:17.840 --> 54:20.640
The wife and I were a little worried about your bonfire.

54:20.640 --> 54:21.400
Oh?

54:21.400 --> 54:23.960
Yes, it is very close to our fence.

54:23.960 --> 54:26.480
The wife and I were worried that it might catch fire.

54:26.480 --> 54:27.440
Don't worry.

54:27.440 --> 54:29.320
Everything is under control.

54:29.320 --> 54:30.280
Where is your wife?

54:30.280 --> 54:31.480
She's not with you.

54:31.480 --> 54:34.880
No, no, she doesn't like to go out in the dark.

54:34.880 --> 54:37.400
Never know who you might meet.

54:37.400 --> 54:39.920
We need to have a quick glass of mulled wine.

54:39.920 --> 54:42.800
Oh, that's very nice of you.

54:42.800 --> 54:44.720
Very nice.

54:44.720 --> 54:46.640
Ooh, hoo, hoo, hoo.

54:46.640 --> 54:48.400
Aren't nice to see you.

54:48.400 --> 54:49.840
Can't sit here.

54:49.840 --> 54:54.720
The mulled wine is very nice, but it's not too strong.

54:54.720 --> 54:57.760
I mean, so strong.

54:57.760 --> 54:59.360
Nice to see you too.

54:59.360 --> 55:01.360
I feel like Darcy.

55:01.360 --> 55:03.880
Josie, play that I swells.

55:03.880 --> 55:06.560
It was nice that Darcy would be a curdle.

55:06.560 --> 55:08.200
It would be my pleasure.

55:08.200 --> 55:09.040
Come on.

55:09.040 --> 55:10.840
Ooh, this is so exciting.

55:15.480 --> 55:17.560
Hmm, play Darcy well together.

55:21.760 --> 55:23.920
I hope Grandma knows where she's leading him.

55:23.920 --> 55:25.480
What do you mean, Josie?

55:25.480 --> 55:26.200
Nothing.

55:26.200 --> 55:27.520
Nothing.

55:27.560 --> 55:28.560
Oh, no.

55:28.560 --> 55:29.760
Careful, Mum.

55:29.760 --> 55:30.920
Look behind you.

55:30.920 --> 55:33.560
What, as you say, I can't hear you.

55:33.560 --> 55:34.320
I have...

55:34.320 --> 55:38.600
Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh.

55:38.600 --> 55:39.880
Leave it to me, Darcy.

55:39.880 --> 55:41.080
I was in the air for hair.

55:41.080 --> 55:42.880
Help me, help me.

55:42.880 --> 55:45.240
Ooh, I'll tell you how to die.

55:45.240 --> 55:46.080
It's all right.

55:46.080 --> 55:47.080
I'm here.

55:47.080 --> 55:49.120
Ooh, ooh, ooh.

55:49.120 --> 55:50.360
Ooh, thank you.

55:50.360 --> 55:51.760
Ooh, I'm rescued.

55:51.760 --> 55:52.760
Thank you.

55:52.760 --> 55:54.200
All right, Mother.

55:54.200 --> 55:55.680
Yes, Darcy.

55:55.680 --> 55:58.160
Just wet and very cold.

55:58.160 --> 55:59.720
Come on upstairs.

55:59.720 --> 56:01.080
And you, Colonel.

56:01.080 --> 56:04.920
I can get you both some dry clothes.

56:04.920 --> 56:05.960
What happened, Josie?

56:05.960 --> 56:08.840
I didn't know your grandmother liked snorkeling in November.

56:08.840 --> 56:10.680
She had too much mold wine.

56:10.680 --> 56:11.720
Oh, dear.

56:11.720 --> 56:12.720
What a pity.

56:12.720 --> 56:14.160
The Colonel is well.

56:14.160 --> 56:16.680
I hope they don't die of pneumonia.

56:16.680 --> 56:19.400
Be so nasty sometimes, Dad.

56:19.400 --> 56:21.080
It's just my sense of humour.

56:21.080 --> 56:21.920
Come on.

56:21.920 --> 56:23.720
Help me with the fireworks for when the beached whales come

56:23.720 --> 56:24.800
downstairs.

56:24.800 --> 56:26.640
Just a moment, Dad.

56:26.640 --> 56:27.600
Back in a minute.

56:27.600 --> 56:32.280
Just want to get some one thing.

56:32.280 --> 56:34.720
Sorry?

56:34.720 --> 56:39.800
Sometimes I think I'm the only normal person in this family.

56:39.800 --> 56:42.040
Here I am.

56:42.040 --> 56:43.520
Much better music, eh?

56:43.520 --> 56:45.600
You know your mother doesn't like it.

56:45.600 --> 56:47.320
Doesn't matter.

56:47.320 --> 56:48.640
I want to like a firework.

56:48.640 --> 56:49.920
I don't know about that.

56:49.920 --> 56:51.200
Oh, come on, Dad.

56:51.200 --> 56:52.840
Only one.

56:52.840 --> 56:54.400
I want to set off a rocket.

56:54.400 --> 56:55.920
OK, but be careful.

56:55.920 --> 56:57.280
No stress.

56:57.280 --> 57:00.600
Josie, what is looking out of your pocket?

57:00.600 --> 57:03.080
Is that...

57:03.080 --> 57:04.080
It's that rat.

57:07.520 --> 57:08.880
Stop it, Dad.

57:08.880 --> 57:09.560
Come here.

57:09.560 --> 57:10.400
Give it to me.

57:10.400 --> 57:11.320
I told you.

57:11.320 --> 57:11.880
Stop it!

57:11.880 --> 57:12.800
Be careful!

57:12.800 --> 57:13.800
The rocket.

57:18.240 --> 57:19.480
What happened?

57:19.480 --> 57:20.840
Are you both all right?

57:20.840 --> 57:21.800
It's that rat.

57:21.800 --> 57:22.760
It's still alive.

57:22.760 --> 57:24.280
Dad tried to kill Robbie.

57:24.280 --> 57:25.640
I told you to sell that rat.

57:25.640 --> 57:26.240
I hate it.

57:26.240 --> 57:27.440
It's vermin.

57:27.440 --> 57:28.480
I don't want to sell it.

57:28.480 --> 57:31.640
It's a strange smell of burning coming from somewhere.

57:31.640 --> 57:33.440
Are you cooking one of your casseroles, Nancy?

57:33.440 --> 57:35.840
No, I'm not.

57:35.840 --> 57:37.680
Where did the rocket go?

57:37.680 --> 57:39.560
I didn't see it in the sky.

57:39.560 --> 57:41.600
I think it was over the fence.

57:41.600 --> 57:43.920
It's an ex-dars guy.

57:43.920 --> 57:46.920
No one was hurt.

57:46.920 --> 57:47.920
Look!

57:47.920 --> 57:48.920
Oh, no!

57:48.920 --> 57:50.080
My shed!

57:50.080 --> 57:51.480
My shed is on fire!

57:51.480 --> 57:52.000
Help!

57:52.000 --> 57:53.760
Help, come on, help!

57:54.760 --> 57:57.400
What a lovely bump I had, Exner.

57:57.400 --> 57:58.840
That's not a bonfire, Mum.

57:58.840 --> 58:00.720
It's a real fire.

58:00.720 --> 58:02.400
Phone the fire brigade, Pete.

58:02.400 --> 58:03.400
Come on, everyone!

58:03.400 --> 58:04.240
Get a bucket!

58:04.240 --> 58:05.200
Come with me!

58:05.200 --> 58:06.200
OK.

58:06.200 --> 58:07.200
Where's the phone?

58:07.200 --> 58:08.200
It's absolutely typical.

58:08.200 --> 58:09.840
When you want something, you can never find it.

58:09.840 --> 58:10.840
There it is.

58:10.840 --> 58:11.840
Behind you, on the bench.

58:11.840 --> 58:12.840
Ah, yes.

58:12.840 --> 58:13.840
Who put it there?

58:13.840 --> 58:14.840
Nine.

58:14.840 --> 58:15.840
Nine.

58:15.840 --> 58:16.840
Nine.

58:16.840 --> 58:17.840
Hello.

58:17.840 --> 58:19.840
What hung out Chinese?

58:19.840 --> 58:20.840
Come on again.

58:21.200 --> 58:22.760
Come on again.

58:22.760 --> 58:24.440
The Chinese take away again.

58:24.440 --> 58:25.640
Yes, what a day.

58:25.640 --> 58:26.640
What a day.

58:26.640 --> 58:29.040
This is a day to remember, I think.

58:29.040 --> 58:30.600
Yes, you're right.

58:30.600 --> 58:33.840
Still, there is one positive result.

58:33.840 --> 58:34.840
Ha-ha.

58:34.840 --> 58:36.440
Please tell me what that is.

58:36.440 --> 58:39.040
I think the days are disaster.

58:39.040 --> 58:42.600
The lawnmower was in the shed.

58:42.600 --> 58:47.320
So, of course you were right.

58:47.320 --> 58:50.040
No more lawnmowering early in the morning.

58:50.040 --> 58:52.040
Just for a few weeks, anyway.

